I think the confusion only comems from the point that this disscussion is acctually not about the cahnge in this commit anymore, but about some text which has been there before already.

I think we talk about the same things and we generally agree on the changes to be made. The only additonal thing I wanted to point out, is that in the case where a user uses the GitHub Service (instead of the plain WebHook) he has not the cance to select the encoding type - thats it. But with the alignement to the Bitbucket implementation this will not make any difference anymore.

@faulkner actually you are confusing github service and webhooks.
After my latest fix there won't be any issues if no X-Github-Event header is specified which is the case for services.

For now github has actually added the header to their service as well.

